In Acumatica ERP, item classes are used to group stock or non-stock items with similar properties and to provide default settings for new items. You can create hierarchical item classes to support a tree-like structure of items grouped by categories and subcategories.{br}
In this section, you will find information about configuration and management of hierarchical item classes. ==In This Section==[anchor|#_c3132788-ef38-47ac-868a-322b4534349b] {| class="checklist invisiblechecklist" | width="100%" |- | [anchor|#_a8428b8e-c1f0-4431-9b98-a6c939c571b5] *[HelpRoot_InvMgmt\IN__con_Hierarchy_of_Item_Classes|Hierarchy of Item Classes ]
