*[HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_45_00|Item Warehouse Details] ([~/?ScreenId=IN204500|IN204500])
*[HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_50_20_00|Update Standard Costs] ([~/?ScreenId=IN502000|IN502000])

For effective inventory management, your company needs to know the value of the inventory at its warehouses. Acumatica ERP implements the perpetual system of maintaining the cost of inventory. With perpetual inventory system, your company can know the quantity of inventory on hand, its cost and the cost of goods sold at any moment of time.{br}{TOC} ==Multiple Valuation Methods== Under the perpetual inventory system, the balance of the account Inventory (or multiple inventory accounts used for different warehouses or classes or groups of items) is updated with each sale or purchase transaction. Each time your company purchases stock items, the inventory account is debited for the cost of items; each time your company sells the items, the inventory account is credited for the cost of sold items.{br}
Under the perpetual inventory system, you can use inventory valuation (cost flow) methods to define how unit costs are determined for each inventory item on issues, thus allowing the system to maintain a correct, up-to-date inventory cost. You can use the following valuation methods: *Standard cost *Average *First-in-first-out (FIFO) *Specific
You assign valuation methods to stock items in the following ways: *By using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_10_00|Item Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=IN201000|IN201000]) form, you can assign a valuation method to a class, which will be used for the items of the class. *By using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_25_00|Stock Items] ([~/?ScreenId=IN202500|IN202500]) form, you can assign a valuation method to a particular item, if you want to override the valuation method of its item class.
The valuation methods are discussed in detail in [HelpRoot_InvMgmt\IN__con_Item_Costs_and_Valuation_Methods|Item Costs and Valuation Methods]. ==Negative Quantities== In the Inventory module, a negative quantity of an inventory item of a specific item class is allowed at a location as long as the quantity on hand is positive. Appropriate warnings are issued on transactions that result in negative quantities. The '''Allow Negative Quantity''' check box is located in the '''General Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_10_00|Item Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=IN201000|IN201000]) form.((({S:Hint}This check box can be applied to items with the standard cost, average cost, and FIFO valuation methods. You cannot apply this check box to items with lot or serial numbers assigned. ))) Negative quantities on hand can result when an issue has been made before the release of the receipt reflecting the arrival of a certain quantity of the inventory item. In this case, for the over-issued quantity, a new layer is created. The cost assigned to the layer is the most recent historical cost of the item. When the inventory is actually received (on receipt in question release), the system compares the cost on the over-issue layer with the cost on the receipt, and generates a cost adjustment for the difference multiplied by the quantity on the layer (the quantity of over-issued units). ==Inventory Valuation and Revaluation== You can review the cost of inventory on hand by using the [HelpRoot_ReportReference\IN_61_55_00|Inventory Valuation] ([~/?ScreenId=IN615500|IN615500]) and [HelpRoot_ReportReference\IN_61_70_00|Historical Inventory Valuation] ([~/?ScreenId=IN617000|IN617000]) reports.{br}
Generally, standard costs are revised at the end of the financial year based on the year’s financial results, although they can be updated more often. The pending standard costs and their effective dates are entered manually for each inventory item that uses this valuation method on the '''Price/Cost Information''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_25_00|Stock Items] ([~/?ScreenId=IN202500|IN202500]) form.{br}
You can run the process of updating the standard costs with the pending standard costs for multiple inventory items by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_50_20_00|Update Standard Costs] ([~/?ScreenId=IN502000|IN502000]) form. For items whose standard costs are being updated, revaluation of their cost is performed. The system generates a batch of transactions that increase or decrease the balance of the inventory accounts, depending on whether the pending costs are greater or less than the current costs and updates the Standard Cost Revaluation accounts defined by the item’s posting class. ==Inclusion of Tax Amounts in Costs for Stock Items== You can configure the system to include use taxes, sales taxes of the ''Input'' group, and partially deductible VATs in the cost of the stock items being purchased. For tax amounts to be included in the costs of items in purchase orders, the following actions must be completed in the system:[anchor|#_ddb0a59a-4b7e-4638-bb69-615e81152c5a] *A tax reason code of the ''Adjustment'' type must be defined on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_21_10_00|Reason Codes] ([~/?ScreenId=CS211000|CS211000]) form, and specified as the '''Tax Reason Code''' on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_10_10_00|Purchase Orders Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=PO101000|PO101000]) form. *In the tax settings on the '''GL Accounts''' tab. on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\TX_20_50_00|Taxes] ([~/?ScreenId=TX205000|TX205000]) form, the '''Use Tax Expense Account''' check box must be cleared.
For a stock item with the ''Average'', ''Specific'', or ''FIFO'' valuation method, on release of an AP bill prepared for a purchase order that includes the item, an inventory adjustment transaction is automatically generated to post the tax amounts to the item&rsquo;s inventory account.{br}
The system shows the link to the generated inventory adjustment transaction in the '''Adjustment Nbr.''' box on the '''Financial Details''' tab on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_10_00|Bills and Adjustments] ([~/?ScreenId=AP301000|AP301000]) form for the AP bill. On release of the inventory adjustment, the system generates the following GL transactions:[anchor|#_4c56cf01-38a9-47a7-9378-d043078628bc] *Inventory Account, Dr, Tax Amount *PO Accrual account, Cr, Tax Amount ((({S:Warn}For partially deductible VAT taxes, only the expense part is posted to the item&rsquo;s inventory account. ))) For stock items with the ''Standard'' valuation method, in the GL transaction generated on release of the AP bill that includes the items, the tax amount is posted directly to the account defined by the '''Tax Reason Code'''. For more information on including taxes in the cost of items, see [HelpRoot_Financials\Taxes_Including_Tax_to_Item_Cost_GeneralInfo|Taxes Included in the Cost of Items: General Information]. ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_InvMgmt\IN__con_Planning_for_Physical_Inventory|Configuration of Physical Inventory] *[HelpRoot_InvMgmt\IN__con_Physical_Inventory_Counts|Physical Inventory Counts] *[HelpRoot_InvMgmt\IN__con_Item_Costs_and_Valuation_Methods|Item Costs and Valuation Methods] *[HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_10_00|Item Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=IN201000|IN201000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_25_00|Stock Items] ([~/?ScreenId=IN202500|IN202500]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_60_00|Posting Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=IN206000|IN206000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_50_20_00|Update Standard Costs] ([~/?ScreenId=IN502000|IN502000]) *[HelpRoot_ReportReference\IN_61_55_00|Inventory Valuation] ([~/?ScreenId=IN615500|IN615500]) *[HelpRoot_ReportReference\IN_61_70_00|Historical Inventory Valuation] ([~/?ScreenId=IN617000|IN617000])

Physical inventory is an important process in organizations that store stock items. This chapter provides you with detailed information about performing physical inventory counts in Acumatica ERP. ==In This Chapter==[anchor|#_d79385b9-1fe3-4b65-917b-624ee1601212] {| class="checklist invisiblechecklist" | width="100%" |- | [anchor|#ul_alp_gr1_zl] *[HelpRoot_InvMgmt\IN__con_Physical_Inventory_Counts|Physical Inventory Counts] *[HelpRoot_InvMgmt\IN__con_Preparation_for_Physical_Count|Preparation for Physical Count]
