Suppose that on March 1, ABC company first purchased a new gadget for bikers (the ''New Gadget'' stock item) and sold it to a local sporting goods store, Best Sports. Best Sports decided to order 200 units during April and May. {br}
The ABC company&rsquo;s purchasing manager, who is responsible for sales of the ''New Gadget'' item, decided to use the following default replenishment parameters during these three months of sales:[anchor|#ul_jkb_m4v_ft] *'''Safety Stock''': 20 *'''Reorder Point''': 50 *'''Max Quantity:''' 200
These parameters were specified for the ''New Gadget'' stock item on the '''Replenishment Info''' tab on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_25_00|Stock Items] ([~/?ScreenId=IN202500|IN202500]) form. {br}
Before extending the sales to other customers, the purchasing manager has decided to collect the relevant sales data during the first three months and then calculate the replenishment parameters based on this data using the following settings:[anchor|#ul_p4w_qtd_ht] *'''Forecast Type''': ''Month'' * '''Periods to Analyze''': ''3'' * '''Launch Date''': ''March 1'' The purchasing manager tracks the New Gadget related events and collects the data as follows.[anchor|#table_zwm_3gv_ft] ===Timeline of purchasing, receiving, and replenishing New Gadget=== {| class="checklist" | width="100%" |- !width="22%" ! Business Date !width="77%" ! Business Event |- | colspan="2" | '''March''' |- | March 1 | ABC company prepares replenishment for New Gadget. |- | March 1 | Purchase order for 200 units of New Gadget is created, approved and sent to the New Gadget vendor. |- | March 15 | The Best Sports store places a sales order for 200 units. |- | March 21 | ABC company receives 200 units of New Gadget. Purchase receipt for 200 units is released. |- | March 22 | Shipment to the Best Sports store is confirmed. |- | March 31 | ABC company collects the data:{br}
''Total Sales: 200 units; Daily Demand: 200/31=6.45; Lead Time: 20'' |- | colspan="2" | '''April''' |- | April 1 | ABC company prepares replenishment for New Gadget. |- | April 1 | Purchase order for 200 units of New Gadget is created, approved and sent to the New Gadget vendor. |- | April 15 | The Best Sports store places a sales order for 200 units. |- | April 18 | ABC company receives 200 units of New Gadget. Purchase receipt for 200 units is released. |- | April 22 | Shipment to the Best Sports store is confirmed. |- | April 30 | ABC company collects the data:{br}
''Total Sales: 200 units; Daily Demand: 200/30=6.67; Lead Time: 17'' |- | colspan="2" | '''May''' |- | May 1 | ABC company prepares replenishment for New Gadget. |- | May 1 | Purchase order for 200 units of New Gadget is created, approved and sent to the New Gadget vendor. |- | May 15 | ABC company receives 200 units of New Gadget. Purchase receipt for 200 units is released. |- | May 15 | The Best Sports store places a sales order for 200 units. |- | May 22 | Shipment to the Best Sports store is confirmed. |- | May 31 | ABC company collects the data:{br}
''Total Sales: 200 units; Daily Demand: 200/31=6.45; Lead Time: 14'' |- | colspan="2" | '''June''' |- | June 1 | The ABC company uses the collected data to calculate the replenishment parameters. |} On June 1, the purchasing manager initiates the calculation of replenishment parameters by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_50_85_00|Calculate Replenishment Parameters] ([~/?ScreenId=IN508500|IN508500]) form. The service level for the New Gadget stock item is selected as 90%.{br}
The system calculated the replenishment parameters as follows.[anchor|#_ce968296-e6ef-4b0d-a7bd-5b28aabcb85e] {| class="checklist" | width="100%" |- !width="33%" ! Parameter !width="33%" ! Suggested Values !width="33%" ! Explanation |- | Average Daily Demand | 6.52 | (200 + 200 + 200) / (31 + 30 + 31) |- | STDEVP(Daily Demand) | 0.10 | STDEVP(200/31, 200/30, 200/31) |- | Average Lead Time | 17 | (20 + 17 + 14 ) / 3 |- | STDEVP(Lead Time) | 2.45 | STDEVP(20, 17, 14) |- | Service Level | 90% | |- | Normsinv(Service Level) | 1.28 | |- | Safety Stock | 20.6 | 1.28 &#42; SQRT((17 &#42; 0.1) ^ 2 + (6.52 &#42; 2.45) ^ 2) |- | Reorder Point | 131.49 | (17 &#42; 6.52 + 20.6) |- | Max. Quantity | 131.49 | |}As this simple example shows, the reorder point should be increased to 131 units mostly due to a rather large average lead time.
